METHODS: The genomic sequences of 134 S. pyogenes isolates from 21 clusters of infection in elderly care or maternity settings from 2010 to 2015 were analysed using bioinformatics to ascertain genomic phylogeny, single nucleotide polymorphism (SNP) differences and statistical outliers from epidemiologically defined outbreaks. Analysis was undertaken within clusters and compared with sporadic isolates from geographically distinct outbreaks of S. pyogenes infection.
